intro: Oreopanax anchicayanus, commonly known as the Anchicaya oreopanax, is a species of flowering plant in the family Araliaceae. It is native to the Andean regions of Ecuador and is characterized by its large, palmate leaves and distinctive, clustered inflorescences. The plant typically grows in humid, shaded environments at moderate elevations. Its botanical features include a woody stem, compound leaves with five to seven lobes, and small, greenish-white flowers that are clustered in umbels. The species is of interest to botanists due to its unique morphology and limited distribution.
